To the Lighthouse

Let me kneel among
the soft grass and weave
clovers and daisies.
The lighthouse stands tall,
a sentinel to mark
the edge of the sea
and land; the horizon stretches
in whispers and remembrance,
a love promised to return.

— H.D.

- HD
